<div id="review_86675381" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/86675381" />
    <a title="Dirk Grobbelaar" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3102740-dirk-grobbelaar"><img alt="Dirk Grobbelaar" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1545117991p2/3102740.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/86675381?book_show_action=true">Jan 25, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dirk Grobbelaar" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dirk Grobbelaar" href="/user/show/3102740-dirk-grobbelaar">Dirk Grobbelaar</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781857231694" href="/book/show/835052.Ringworld">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3102740-dirk-grobbelaar?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3102740-dirk-grobbelaar?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3102740-dirk-grobbelaar?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3102740-dirk-grobbelaar?shelf=hugo-award-winners">hugo-award-winners</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3102740-dirk-grobbelaar?shelf=nebula-award-winners">nebula-award-winners</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3102740-dirk-grobbelaar?shelf=55essential-space-opera-barnesnoble">55essential-space-opera-barnesnoble</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer86675381" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1415876152163920545">Not much I can say about this. <br/><br/>It blew my mind.<br/><br/>In order for you to <b>truly</b> appreciate <i>Ringworld</i> you would have to mentally backtrack forty-odd years. <br/><br/>Big Ideas in Science Fiction are a dime a dozen. <br/><b>Today.</b><br/><br/>But in 1970…?<br/><br/>Perhaps Niven’s vision upstaged his characters. Perhaps. But I could still lose myself on the <b>ring</b>. It fascinated me then; it fascinates me now. This novel made authors sit up and pay attention to just how big you could think if you really applied your imagination. Also, I’ve spent y</span>
  <span id="freeText1415876152163920545" style="display:none">Not much I can say about this. <br /><br />It blew my mind.<br /><br />In order for you to <b>truly</b> appreciate <i>Ringworld</i> you would have to mentally backtrack forty-odd years. <br /><br />Big Ideas in Science Fiction are a dime a dozen. <br /><b>Today.</b><br /><br />But in 1970…?<br /><br />Perhaps Niven’s vision upstaged his characters. Perhaps. But I could still lose myself on the <b>ring</b>. It fascinated me then; it fascinates me now. This novel made authors sit up and pay attention to just how big you could think if you really applied your imagination. Also, I’ve spent years wracking my mind trying to think just how that <b>horizon</b> must look, curving up like that for millions of miles…<br /><br /><b>Hugo Award – 1970</b><br /><b>Nebula Award – 1971</b><br /><b>Locus Award – 1971</b><br /><br /><b>Respect</b><br /><br /><i>Loved it then</i><br /><i>Love it now</i><br /><i>Favourites</i> <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1415876152163920545" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


