        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1126353467" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9838120834980896499">&quot;Read <i>Ringworld</i>!&quot; she said.<br/>&quot;Read <i>Ringworld</i>!&quot; he implored. <br/>&quot;Read <i>Ringworld</i> you lazy muthafucka!&quot; I chided myself. <br/>&quot;Okay already! I&apos;ll read it. Now lay off!&quot; other me shouted back.<br/><br/>Larry Niven sci-fi classic is not filled with a lot of action. It&apos;s mostly about exploration, some space theory and some alien character development. By the time you&apos;re done with it, you can definitely see that this is just the tip of the iceberg, and the series that followed makes sense. <br/><br/>I really enjoyed this, but I kno</span>
  <span id="freeText9838120834980896499" style="display:none">"Read <i>Ringworld</i>!" she said.<br />"Read <i>Ringworld</i>!" he implored. <br />"Read <i>Ringworld</i> you lazy muthafucka!" I chided myself. <br />"Okay already! I'll read it. Now lay off!" other me shouted back.<br /><br />Larry Niven sci-fi classic is not filled with a lot of action. It's mostly about exploration, some space theory and some alien character development. By the time you're done with it, you can definitely see that this is just the tip of the iceberg, and the series that followed makes sense. <br /><br />I really enjoyed this, but I know some people have complained about it's humorous side. It's no <i>Hitchhiker's Guide...</i> but perhaps it is a bit silly at times. That didn't bother me. The preponderance of theory tends to drag down the excitement level at times, so I was glad for a bit of lightheartedness now and then. <br /><br />The main characters are well-defined, so that by the midway point I could probably have guessed who was speaking without dialogue tags. They were enjoyable people to spend a novel's worth of time with, and I could see myself moving on to the next book to see where their lives lead them.</span>
